I don't know how you put someone in a position to

00:00:16.540 --> 00:00:19.220
become more empathetic or compassionate. That's an intrinsic thing. That's

00:00:19.220 --> 00:00:21.680
not something you can just read in a book and you naturally have

00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:25.500
love for someone else, or care for someone else who is struggling.

00:00:25.510 --> 00:00:35.700
interdisciplinary team with nurses, outreach workers. We get

00:00:36.260 --> 00:00:40.860
support from psychiatry in the hospital as well and we liaison with

00:00:41.480 --> 00:00:45.180
prescribers of the community. We are always advocating for clients in the

00:00:45.180 --> 00:00:47.980
emergency department whether that be a certification to

00:00:48.540 --> 00:00:52.620
psychiatry or a medical floor, whatever the case may be.

00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:56.940
We work with the individual as through their stay in hospital and try

00:00:56.940 --> 00:01:01.460
to have them land in community as gently as possible upon discharge.

